## 5. Regulatory frameworks (ABS / UPG / SRF)

**Product intent:** Analysis should be grounded in **ABS** (Australian Banking Code style practice), **UPG** (unauthorised payment / protected-account style framing), and **SRF** (Singapore shared responsibility / scam-assisted flows).

**Schema reality:** There is **no separate ABS table**. Authoritative text and clause units live in **`regulatory_documents`** and **`regulatory_clauses`**, with **`embedding`** populated (e.g. via [[backfill embeddings v1]]) so **`match_regulatory_clauses`** / **`match_regulatory_clauses_threshold`** can retrieve context for decisioning.

**Action:** ingest ABS / other corpora into those tables + embeddings — same pipeline as other regulators.

