## Core Fields

### Identity
- `id` — unique content record
- `document_id` — parent document

---

### Parsing / Processing
- `model` — model used for parsing (OCR / AI)
- `prompt_version` — parsing prompt version
- `pipeline_version` — overall pipeline version

---

### Content
- `text_content` — full extracted text
- `content_json` — structured representation of content

---

### Metadata
- `language`
- `page_count`
- `parsed_at`

---

### Status
- `parse_status` — success / failed / partial
- `parse_errors` — errors encountered

---

### Integrity
- `content_sha256` — hash of parsed content

---

## How It Is Used

Content records are:

1. Created after document upload
2. Used as input for:
   - chunking (`case_document_chunks`)
   - extraction pipelines
   - embeddings / RAG

---

## Relationship to Other Tables

- `case_documents` → raw file
- `case_documents_content` → parsed content
- `case_document_chunks` → segmented content

This is the **middle transformation layer**.

